---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="My Beloved Lash"
  description="Built and operated a service business from concept to operation, overseeing project management, team leadership, systems development, marketing, and daily operations."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Experience</p>

    <h1>My Beloved Lash</h1>

    <p class="intro">
      Built and operated a service business from concept to operation,
      overseeing commercial build-out, team leadership, process development,
      marketing, and daily business operations.
    </p>

    <p class="meta">
      Operations Manager • November 2021 – May 2026
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>

    <p>
      My Beloved Lash began as an idea to create a better experience for both
      clients and service providers. What started as a concept eventually grew
      into a fully operational business serving hundreds of clients and
      supporting a team of lash technicians and front desk staff.
    </p>

    <p>
      Over the course of building and operating the business, I was responsible
      for nearly every aspect of development and operations, including site
      selection, permitting, construction, hiring, process development,
      marketing, technology implementation, and day-to-day management.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Business Development & Project Management</h2>

    <p>
      Establishing the salon required coordinating a commercial build-out from
      the ground up. Responsibilities included identifying and securing a
      location, negotiating lease terms, designing the salon layout, obtaining
      permits and approvals, and coordinating with contractors, engineers,
      inspectors, and township officials.
    </p>

    <p>
      I created the salon layout in SketchUp and worked alongside a licensed
      engineer to prepare construction documentation for approval. Throughout
      the project, I managed timelines, budgets, inspections, and regulatory
      requirements necessary to open the business.
    </p>

    <p>
      The completed facility included five treatment rooms, a supply room, and
      a dedicated training and meeting space designed to support both daily
      operations and future employee development.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Operations & Team Leadership</h2>

    <p>
      As the business grew, I managed a team of up to six employees, including
      five technicians and a front desk coordinator. Responsibilities included
      hiring, onboarding, scheduling, payroll, performance management, customer
      service, inventory management, vendor coordination, budgeting, and daily
      operational oversight.
    </p>

    <p>
      Maintaining consistent service quality required balancing the needs of
      both employees and clients while ensuring the business continued to
      operate efficiently. This experience strengthened my ability to lead
      teams, communicate expectations, solve problems, and make decisions in
      fast-moving situations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Systems & Process Development</h2>

    <p>
      To support growth and consistency, I developed operational systems and
      policies that standardized many aspects of the business. These included
      employee onboarding procedures, technician handbooks, appointment
      policies, client intake processes, automated communications, and internal
      workflows.
    </p>

    <p>
      These systems reduced administrative burden, improved consistency, and
      helped create a more predictable experience for both employees and
      clients. Maintaining organized processes became increasingly important as
      the client base expanded.
    </p>

    <p>
      Over time, the business accumulated more than 870 client profiles and
      served a steady volume of recurring appointments each week.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Marketing & Technology</h2>

    <p>
      I managed the business's digital presence and customer acquisition
      efforts through website development, search engine optimization (SEO),
      social media marketing, email campaigns, and paid advertising.
    </p>

    <p>
      Responsibilities also included managing online scheduling systems,
      payment processing platforms, domain registration, website hosting, and
      customer communication tools. These efforts helped establish a
      professional customer experience while supporting business growth and
      retention.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>

    <p>
      Running a business taught me that success depends on understanding both
      the people you work with and the people you serve. Employees need clear
      expectations, support, and systems that help them perform their work
      effectively, while customers need a reliable and consistent experience.
    </p>

    <p>
      Building an organization that serves both groups well requires
      communication, accountability, process development, and continuous
      improvement. These lessons strengthened my leadership abilities and
      continue to influence how I approach problem-solving, project management,
      and teamwork today.
    </p>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  section + section {
    margin-top: 4rem;
  }

  .hero {
    max-width: 48rem;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .meta {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
</style>